<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[264,1325,284,1150]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis box="[312,414,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks</emphasis>
: The apophysis of the style in the 
<typeStatus box="[840,941,924,950]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">paratype</typeStatus>
male is much longer and more slender and the aedeagal shaft is also slightly longer than in the 
<typeStatus box="[1014,1117,964,990]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">holotype</typeStatus>
male. 
<taxonomicName box="[1198,1322,964,989]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis box="[1198,1322,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">S. hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the coloration of the species of 
<taxonomicName box="[705,850,1004,1029]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[705,850,1004,1029]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Scaphotettix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is unique in having numerous long (almost twice as long as the subgenital plate) hairlike setae on the submarginal plate, to which the specific name alludes. It shares the basally fused paraphyses with 
<taxonomicName box="[1157,1278,1084,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hussa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis box="[1157,1278,1084,1109]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">S. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in colour and, male genital structure and is also a smaller species.
</paragraph>
